metadata.name: Stoner Stick People Series 2
metadata.description:
The other day I was finally inspired to pick up the Stoner Stick People and again venture off into places I hadn't been, trying new things. I wanted to do more than I'd done before, a promise to myself, and it took a minute for something to click. Color. Not just little bits, but entire environments, Vibes, for Stoners to just, well, Vibe in. The way I wanted to vibe. Be distracted and free my mind to go to the places where it needed to. Needs to.

Another experiment in learning how to layer and play with...lots, lol. I hope y'all enjoy Series 2 :)

Puff puff pass.

Wessel '22

metadata.name: zero-player stained glass
metadata.description:
After selecting nodes by poisson disc sampling, a voronoi grid was created and cyclic cellular automata were applied to this grid. Unlike the case of applying cyclic celluar automata to the rect grid, the wave does not continue and disappears gradually.

keyboard controls:
[s] - Get an image of 600 x 600 px.
[d] - Get an image of 1200 x 1200 px. (2x magnification)

metadata.name: Possessed Samurai
metadata.description:
**** (if you are on a mobile device such as a smartphone or tablet, please open the artwork in live view and zoom in for best experience) *****


Inspired by Japanese and Indonesian (Bali) Artworks, this generative artwork tries to capture the soul of an ancient warrior.

The outer and inner layer of the eyes have random rotational values corresponding to each hash. They create some amazing and unique pieces, in combination with the randomly generated color schemes. The overall effect is one of awe.

This piece was made entirely with code through P5.js library.

This is my first art piece on fxhash. If you enjoy my work, I shall release more pieces. Thanks and have fun!

metadata.name: Fauve is legion
metadata.description:
Fauve is legion. Fauve is crowd. Fauve is pressure.

Fauve is a collection open for interpretation. It explores the feeling of gathering many entities in a tight space. These circle entities seem to be looking straight back at you, waiting for something to happen.
If these entites were humans, what do you think they would feel in this moment?
What do you feel when you look at them?

metadata.name: Errors IV // Seasons
metadata.description:
The idea behind this project is to juxtapose two different frames from the same 'roll'. This is a double exposure experiment mixed using a few different blending modes. The double exposure is not done in camera, instead the algorithm will randomly pick two images and blend them.

In this section there are different images from different seasons, the opposition of some of the textures make some amazing ambience compositions. It's very interesting to visualize different distinctive features of each season mixed with each other. 

There are 36 different images on the 'film roll' so it's better to keep the editions low to avoid doubles as much as possible.

Unfortunately due to size restrictions of fxHash the images are not full size, and are limited to 1500px x 1000px.

metadata.name: The Seventh Circle
metadata.description:
The Seventh Circle

"Now I would have you know: the other time
that I descended into lower Hell,
this mass of boulders had not yet collapsed."


- The canvas is split into between 64 and 256 areas. Each area is separated from its neighbours by a border of between 1.5% and 4.5% of the canvas.

- Each area is further subdivided into between 64 and 100 smaller squares. These are separated by a proportionally-smaller border.

- A time-based function affects the hue of each square, mapping the sin and cosine of each squares position, offset by an amount determined from the initial hash. Over time, the colour of the squares will change, dependent on further initial values.

- Occasionally, sections of each grid will break away, rendering at an angle to the main piece. Within this, individual squares may be rotated slightly.

- The overlaid texture may be dark or bright, horizontally or vertically. The texture size may vary according to the initial conditions.


Most importantly, with the fullness of time, all pieces have a chance of returning to wholeness; they are all a part of a cycle of life, that each one may know its place.

Almost anything can be forgiven.

metadata.name: Fabrics
metadata.description:
Fabric. A collection of swatches. 

This is a project of stacked PNGs producing fabric swatches. Some are almost plaids, others are more batik, while others are more of a "magic eye" or optical illusion look. 

The PNGs were generated using VBA and conditional formatting in MS Excel, then copy/pasted as an image into MS PowerPoint, and occasionally further manipulated in different image editors including MS Paint. Images were batch resized to match each other at 1125x1125.

There are a lot of options for this collection. The layers and total number of options per (included "none" layers):
- Base
    - 42
- Flecking

Fabric. A collection of swatches. 

This is a project of stacked PNGs producing fabric swatches. Some are almost plaids, others are more batik, while others are more of a "magic eye" or optical illusion look. 

The PNGs were generated using VBA and conditional formatting in MS Excel, then copy/pasted as an image into MS PowerPoint, and occasionally further manipulated in different image editors including MS Paint. Images were batch resized to match each other at 1125x1125.

There are a lot of options for this collection. The layers and total number of options per (included "none" layers):
- Base
    - 42
- Flecking 
    - 18
